reviewText: This is the two-part season two episode from Walker, Texas Ranger that brings takes them down south into Louisiana and the Black Bayou country.  After Walker gets hurts during a drug raid he is told to go on medical leave so he goes down to the bayou to get in some fishing but he gets more than he bargains for when he finds out that drug dealers are in the bayou.  They do not like people snooping around their property and Walker has to deal with flashbacks from Vietnam caused by falling and hitting his head and getting rid of the drug dealers while at the same time protecting  a mother and her son from getting hurt.
thank you very much i like it and it's my favorite
